# Runtime outputs (case-specific, not for version control).
# NOTE: we ignore the CONTENTS (exports/* , analysis/*) rather than the directories
# themselves, so a curated, REAL evidence bundle can be re-included by the allowlist
# at the bottom of this file. Directory-level ignores (exports/, analysis/) would make
# per-file negation impossible (git cannot re-include a file under an excluded dir).
exports/*
analysis/*
/reports/
docs/*.html

# Test cache
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# IDEs
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Forensic images (never commit evidence)
*.raw
*.vmem
*.mem
*.E01
*.e01
*.dd
*.img
*.plaso

# Logs
*.log

# Weasyprint / PDF output
*.pdf

# YARA compiled rules
*.yarc

# Claude Code local settings
.claude/

# Local reference / development materials
additional_details/

# ── Committed per-case chain-of-custody bundles (real investigation runs) ─────
# Everything under analysis/ and exports/ is ignored EXCEPT the per-case bundles below.
# Committing them lets a judge independently run `verify_findings.py` on a fresh clone:
# resolve each finding's audit_id -> the exact tool command + SHA-256 + raw output, and
# recompute the tamper-evident hash chain. Nothing is synthesized; these are the real
# files each run produced, kept at their original paths so the hash chain stays intact.
# We re-include ONLY: the case audit log + findings + hypothesis ledger, and the cited
# raw tool outputs (the top-level *.txt). The bulky EZ-Tools CSV working subdirs
# (exports/<case>/evtx, /shellbags, /lnk, ...) stay ignored.
!analysis/rocba/
analysis/rocba/*
!analysis/rocba/forensic_audit.log
!analysis/rocba/findings.json
!analysis/rocba/hypotheses.json
!exports/rocba/
exports/rocba/*
!exports/rocba/*.txt

!analysis/vanko/
analysis/vanko/*
!analysis/vanko/forensic_audit.log
!analysis/vanko/findings.json
!analysis/vanko/hypotheses.json
!exports/vanko/
exports/vanko/*
!exports/vanko/*.txt

# Sample audit trails for verify_findings.py (*.log global pattern would block these)
!docs/sample/rocba_analysis/forensic_audit.log
!docs/sample/vanko_analysis/forensic_audit.log
